grete myghte & &thorn;e vertue of &thorn;e percyens, whase strenghte
&thorn;ou may neuer sloke&ntail; ne ouercome, suppose &thorn;ou
gadirde & semble&dtail; togedir a&llbar; &thorn;e werlde.  For I do
&thorn;e wele to wiete &thorn;ou myghte nerehan&dtail; alsonne nommer
&thorn;e sternes of heue&ntail;, as &thorn;e folke of &thorn;e empire
of Perse.  Oure godde&yogh; also,<MILESTONE N="7 bk." UNIT="leaf"> by whay&mtail; a&llbar; &thorn;is
werlde es gouerne&dtail; & sustene&dtail;, praysse&yogh; &
commende&yogh; oure name passyng a&llbar; o&thorn;er nacyons.  'Bot
no&yogh;te wit-standynge &thorn;is; &thorn;ou as a litti&llbar; bisne
& a dwerghe, a halfe ma&ntail; & orte&yogh; of a&llbar;e me&ntail;,
desyran&dtail; to ouerpasse &thorn;i litti&llbar;nesse, ri&yogh;te
as a mouse crepe&yogh; oute of hir hole,so &thorn;ou ert crope&ntail;
out of &thorn;e lande of Sethy&mtail;, wenynge wit a few rebawde&yogh;
to conquere & optene &thorn;e lande&yogh; of Perse brade & lange, & to
ryotte & playe the in thay&mtail; as myesse douse in &thorn;e house
whare na cattes ere.  Bot I &thorn;at priualy hase aspie&dtail; thi
