<P>Alexander fra &thorn;e citee of Thebe, went to Corynthe, and
&thorn;are come ti&llbar; hym certane lordes, prayan&dtail; hym
&thorn;at he walde come & see a wrestillynge.  And he graunte&dtail;
&thorn;a&mtail;.  And to &thorn;is Ilke wrestillynge &thorn;are come
folke witowtte&ntail; nowmer.  And whe&ntail; a&llbar; me&ntail; were
gadirde, Alexander saide: 'whilk of &yogh;owe,' quo&thorn; he,
'sa&llbar; gaa & be-gyn&ntail; &thorn;is playe'. Clitomarus
&thorn;a&ntail;, of whay&mtail; I spake bifore, kneli&dtail; bi-fore
&thorn;e kyng, & saide : 'lorde,' quo&thorn; he, '& &yogh;e wolle
vouche-saffe to giffe me leue, I wi&llbar; be-gy&ntail;.'  And
Alexander bad hym ga to.  And Clitomarus went in-to &thorn;e place,
and &thorn;e firste ma&ntail; &thorn;at come in his hande, at the
first tourne he threwe hym wide ope&ntail;.  And Alexander said
vnti&llbar; hym: 'Caste thre me&ntail;,' quo&thorn; he, '& &thorn;ou
sa&llbar; be coroun&dtail;'.  &THORN;a&ntail; &thorn;are come
ano&thorn;er ma&ntail; to Clitomarus and vnnethe&yogh; he come in his
hande&yogh;, whe&ntail; he was caste&ntail; wyde open.  And one
&thorn;e same wyse he seruede &thorn;e thirde.  And &thorn;an
Alexander gart sett o&ntail; his heuede a precious corou&ntail;, and
&thorn;e kynge&yogh; seruaunde&yogh; spirrede hym what his name was.
'My name,' quo&thorn; he, ' es wit owtte&ntail; citee'.  When
Alexander herde &thorn;at he saide vn-ti&llbar; hym: 'Thou noble
wristiller,' quo&thorn; he, 'whi arte &thorn;ou callede wit owtte&ntail; citee.' 'Wirchipfu&llbar; emperour,' quo&thorn; he, be-fore &thorn;at &yogh;e werede &thorn;e emperours Dyademe, I hadde a
citee fu&llbar; of folke&yogh; & of reches.  Bot now, sene &yogh;e
come to this astate & &thorn;is dignytes, I am spoylede & priuede of
my citee.'  And whe&ntail; [he] herde this, he wiste wele &thorn;at he
ment of &thorn;e citee of Thebe.  And &thorn;an he garte his
sergeante&yogh;<MILESTONE N="12" UNIT="leaf"> make a crye that [he] had&dtail; giffen Clitomarus
leue for to repairelle &thorn;e citee of Thebes.  Fra Corinthe,
Alexander and his oste remowe&dtail; ti&llbar; a citee &thorn;at
highte Platea, of &thorn;e whilke a ma&ntail; &thorn;at highte
Scrassageras was prynce.  And Alexander went to &thorn;e temple of
Diane, and fande &thorn;are a woma&ntail; preste, &thorn;e whilke was
a mayde&ntail;, & scho was araie&dtail; lyke preste&yogh; of &thorn;at
tymme.  And whe&ntail; [scho] sawe Alexander, scho saide vn-ti&llbar;
hym: 'Alexander,' quo&thorn; scho, '&thorn;ou
 
<PB N="32">
arte welcomme.  &THORN;ou scha&llbar; conquere a&llbar; &thorn;e
werlde.'  One &thorn;e morne Scrassageras went to &thorn;e same
