hym-warde, and manace&dtail; hym, he wrate vn-to &thorn;a&mtail; a
lettre &thorn;at spak one this wyse.  <Q TYPE="letter"><TEXT>
<BODY>
<P>' Alexander, &thorn;e son of Philippe and of qwene Olympias, vn to
the Athenenes, gretynge.  Fra &thorn;e tyme &thorn;at oure Fadir was
dedde, & we were sett in &thorn;e Trone of his dingnytee, we went into
&thorn;e weste Marches, whare a&llbar; &thorn;e folke&yogh; &thorn;at
duelle&yogh; thare for &thorn;e maste party &yogh;alde &thorn;a&mtail;
vn-ti&llbar; vs wit-owtten stresse.  Fra &thorn;e citee of Rome to
&thorn;e weste see occyane, a&llbar; me&ntail; submytte
&thorn;a&mtail; vn-ti&llbar; vs &thorn;at wit oure awen fre wi&llbar;
we hafe taken &thorn;a&mtail; ti&llbar; oure grace.  And thase
&thorn;at walde no&yogh;te submytt &thorn;a&mtail; ti&llbar; vs wit
fairenes, we hafe distruye&dtail; &thorn;a&mtail; & &thorn;aire
cite&yogh;, and dounge&ntail; &thorn;a&mtail; dow&ntail; to &thorn;e
erthe. And now &thorn;is o&thorn;er daye as we went fra Macedoyne &
passed thurg&hbar; Asye: bi &thorn;e cite of Thebe, &thorn;e Thebeyens
despyse&dtail; vs, & lete as &thorn;ay sett no&yogh;te by vs.  Bot
onane we garte &thorn;air pryde fa&llbar;e, and de-
<PB N="33">
struye&dtail; bathe &thorn;a&mtail; & thaire citee.  And
&thorn;are-fore we write vn-to &yogh;ow; that &yogh;e sende vs
te&ntail; philosop&hbar;res &thorn;at be wyse,<MILESTONE N="12 bk." UNIT="leaf"> by &thorn;e
whilke we may be encensede and conselle&dtail;.  For o&thorn;er thyng
wi&llbar; we nane aske &yogh;ow, Bot a&llbar;e anely &thorn;at
&thorn;e halde vs for &yogh;our lorde & &yogh;our kynge.  And &yogh;if
&yogh;e wi&llbar; no&yogh;te submytt &yogh;owe vn-ti&llbar; vs,
&yogh;ow buse o&thorn;er be strangere &thorn;a&ntail; we, or e&llbar;s
